# Graph Theory

## Euler's Formula for Planar Graphs

$$
V - E + F = 2
$$

Where \(V\) is the number of vertices, \(E\) the number of edges, and \(F\) the number of faces.

## Degree of a Vertex

$$
\text{degree}(v) = \sum_{v \in E} 1
$$

## Adjacency Matrix

Given a graph \(G\), the adjacency matrix \(A\) is defined as:

$$
A[i][j] =
\begin{cases} 
1 & \text{if } (i, j) \in E \\
0 & \text{otherwise} 
\end{cases}
$$
